place.name: AYLESBY
place.gazetteerText: AYLESBY, a parish in Caistor district, Lincoln; on the Wolds, 2½ miles WSW of Great Coates r. station, and 4 W of Great Grimsby. Post Town, Laceby under Grimsby. Acres, 2,110. Real property, £2,851. Pop., 130. Houses, 26. The living is a p. curacy in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £73. Patron, T. T. Drake, Esq. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
